Last year I made a series of hero shots for @fitaideurope and at the end of it decided to combine both signature styles (low key and bold for Rx, and high key and fresh for the original) into one.
If there‚Äôs one thing I learned from my product photography inspirations is that the challenge of ‚Äúgetting it right in-camera‚Äù is one worth chasing. You can photoshop whatever you want later to create a beautiful image, but that kind of fakery should be beneath you if you‚Äôre serious about being a technical artist.
Contrary to what you may think, there‚Äôs no photoshop involved here. It‚Äôs not a composite image, and the sharp line between the deep black and blown white is just the result of using flags, masks, and reflectors where needed to get the shot right in one go.
Just as with the sports we all love... practise pure skills often, and your results will be pure as well.
